metadata.name: Anachronous #37
metadata.description:
This project is about the exploration of chaotic structures created with lines and blurry silhouettes. They work together to make the shapes emerge without revealing them completely and create dark and light areas that compose a feeling of depth and weight to the scene.

Some pieces are chaotic, some more ordered. Some have strong compositions, some don't. By zooming in on the details we can let our mind wander and start seeing shapes.

Best experienced in full-screen.

Press S to take a screenshot
Press M to take a high resolution screenshot
Press H to take a higher resolution screenshot (may not work for some devices)

WARNING: Project is using webgl, it may not work on some older devices.

Original artwork by William Watkins · Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: Collage #243
metadata.description:
Inspired by traditional Japanese wagami design. We use the iconic patterns of our previous projects to recreate this artwork. All the patterns are generated first and then used to build the scene. 

In this project Aluan brings his delicate texture from his 'Chaos' series, Jinyao brings his beloved pattern from the 'Cloud' series and Wen brings his iconic pattern from the 'Maze'. 'Collage' is not just about mixing our style, but it is also about finding harmony among all the elements. 'Collage' is also about working together, in that we can create something that's difficult to achieve or imagine if we were working alone.

Each piece contains the patterns of all the 3 artists, each artist has a certain number of patterns with different colors. Depending which artist you get, his pattern will be shown as the primary color theme while the pattern of the other 2 artists turns into grayscale to make the primary pattern with color stand out. 

There are 7 different scenes included in this project, which are : Mountains, Waves, Lake, Hexagons, Tetrapods, Chrysanthemums and Lotus. We took great inspiration from the traditional Japanese design, and we discovered these are some of the most common elements in it. Therefore we decide to use them and reimagine them by mixing our patterns. 

The title 'Collage' doesn't only apply to the visual style, but also to the code as well. In this project we mixed p5.js and Vanilla JS. While Aluan and Jinyao work with their patterns in p5. Wen gathered the patterns and recreated the full scene in Vanilla JS.

metadata.name: Uncrossed Paths #5
metadata.description:
Many agents start at random locations in random directions (up, down, left or right). There is a small chance that they might turn at any frame. Also, there is a small chance of a new agent being born perpendicular to any agent.
The ultimate rule is, the paths must not be crossed. If an agent comes across its own or another agent’s path, it turns and moves on. If there is no way to go, the agent stops.
The maximum animation time is 22 sec, although most of the token gets completed around 15 sec.
These simple rules, paired with some chosen palettes can generate beautiful figures.

Press r - restart the animation with different settings (primary traits stay the same)
Press s - save 2048x2048 png in live mode

metadata.name: Theatergoers #217
metadata.description:
Simple black and white blobs align to create delicate stories of an audience at their local theater. Follow their eyes in each piece to get started, but don't stare for too long——that's rude.

- press 's' to save the image at its current resolution
- press 'h' to say hello

20% of primary sales will be donated to https://www.cityarts.org/ and minters will receive a small royalty for all secondary sales. 

Made with <3 and p5js | License: CC BY-NC-ND

metadata.name: stranger's gift #6
metadata.description:
A human being is the most intelligent and ambiguous particle of the vast organism, for we are the only ones who, in addition to maintaining common life, have the ability to harm our world and each other. Like any particle, the individual can only be fully aware of his own existence and path.

You are surrounded by people. On the scale there are over seven billion people around you. Most of them you do not know and will never know. Just as you don't think about every drop in the sea, you don't think about the existence of each individual person. A person is not in your own world until he/she/they etc. touches it. But, just as in the current of the sea you may come across a sharp stone or the most beautiful pearl, so in the mass of people you may come across that stranger.
He is a constant variable. You can't recognize him among the faceless landscape until he stands at the edge of your world. At the same time, his figure is sacred and not accidental. You were meant to meet him, and he was meant to meet you.
The Stranger has a gift for you. He can show you what the future holds, or answer questions that have long tormented you. 
This moment is a second before you meet your personal stranger.
Where will you meet him? Will he scare you or charm you? What gift will he give you and why? What will he predict for you?
This will be your personal story. Whether you want to tell it or keep it to yourself is up to you.


Code by PureSpider

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #489
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: The Flirt #6
metadata.description:
What will you give to your lover?

Token made with layers, drawn digitally, randomized by a template.

metadata.name: Gonzion #6
metadata.description:
Gonzion is a Non-Linear Iterated Function System rendered using a method similar to Fractal Flames of Electric Sheep fame.

Technological tendrils from beyond light-aeons draw ancient crystals, transmuted fungus, sentient sigils in fossilized dimensions and alien topologies.

It's not built to run on a (2022) mobile phone and has been known to crash some, but runs fine on others.

For higher resolution renders add "#N" to the URL, default N=2.

metadata.name: Luminous Ocean #2
metadata.description:
Luminous Ocean is a collection based on the bioluminescence phenomenon, in this case the one produced in the ocean.
I used the Flow Fields concept to create it.

There are 18 color palettes for the spheres and rings, which have 2 types of sizes, medium and small.
70% of the background is black.
20% chance that the background will change.
5% chance that the spheres and rings will be bright multicolored.
2% chance of getting a super rare ocean.

Press "S" in live mode to save image 1600x2000.

Created by Fernando. NFT License 2.0.
